Tourism Cabinet Secretary Najib Balala has formed a task force to endear Kenya as a tourism and investment destination.The formation of the task force was mooted during a meeting co-chaired by CS Balala and his Industrialisation counterpart Adan Mohamed and attended by various captains of industry. The task force will be chaired by Equity Bank Chief Executive James Mwangi.&quot;Today, we formed a unique partnership between government and the private sector, to specifically focus on changing the global and local narrative on Kenya and as a result improve the image of Kenya globally and consequently increase tourism inflows, foreign direct investments and possibly the growth of Kenya into a business hub in this part of the world,&quot; he said.Balala said the Ministry of Tourism was allocating Sh200 million to the initiative that will further complement other transformative measures to improve the sector.